   {
      "author_association" : "MEMBER",
      "body" : ">If this isn't a problem with any of the compilers that are realistically used to build bitcoin core, I tend towards NACK. We shouldn't keep old compatibility cruft around forever.\r\n\r\nIt's still linked by current MinGW. Even if it does nothing, it is incorrect to omit it.\r\n\r\nAt the very least, if removing it, we should have some kind of check for a minimum MinGW version, which is probably more complex than just doing the right thing here...\r\n\r\n(Alternatively, if someone wants to put in the time to see if `-mthreads` works correctly with static binaries now, that's probably the *best* route to go)",
      "created_at" : "2020-03-25T14:03:27Z",
      "html_url" : "https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/pull/18427#issuecomment-603857240",
      "id" : 603857240,
